itemDescription: British naval officer and Arctic explorer

wikipedia_page.main: Vice-Admiral Sir George Strong Nares  (24 April 1831 – 15 January 1915) was a Royal Navy officer and Arctic explorer. He commanded the Challenger Expedition, and the British Arctic Expedition. He was highly thought of as a leader and scientific explorer. In later life he worked for the Board of Trade and as Acting Conservator of the River Mersey.
